      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FABIO ZED (7) showed strong early pace and proved too slick around this track over 300m in 17.60, claiming a Grade 4/5 by one length. Winner at his latest appearance in one of the quickest times on the card. Looks to have an edge on most of these. FUN EFFECTS (5) is going well, finishing in the placings twice in a row. Not beaten far last time when a 1.5 lengths third (17.71) in a Grade 4/5 at this track. Rates a winning chance on best. PRINCE ROLEX (4) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (22.86) at Maitland behind Zipping Daly in a Grade 5. Has the pace to be prominent. Will give a great sight again. RITZY RITZY (1) defied the market to win last start and cannot be ruled out.",
